bliss
------------------------------------------
bliss is an open-source tool for computing canonical labelings and
automorphism groups of graphs. Its algorithms are described in the following
papers, please cite them if you use bliss in your research or software tools.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libbliss-devel-0.77-1bl2
  libbliss0-0.77-1bl2
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libgmp-devel-6.3.0-1
  libgmp10-6.3.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libgmp-devel-6.3.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://users.aalto.fi/~tjunttil/bliss/

Canonical download:
  https://users.aalto.fi/~tjunttil/bliss/downloads/bliss-0.77.zip

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bliss-0.77-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bliss-0.77-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bliss-0.77-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bliss-0.77-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbliss0-0.77-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbliss-devel-0.77-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

